TIRANA , July 15 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- A multinational military exercise , the biggest so far in Albania , began today at the Biza military training center built with U.S. assistance .
Albanian President Sali Berisha and defence ministers of Greece and Bulgaria attended the opening ceremony of the exercise code-named `` Peaceful Hawk -96 '' .
<ENAMEX TYPE="OKAY">The exercise , co-commanded by the United States and Albania , involves more than 2,000 servicemen from eight countries</ENAMEX> and is to end on Saturday .
It aims to improve the military coordination among the south-eastern European countries and enhance their capacity to conduct joint peacekeeping operations with NATO .
The exercise is expected to help these states further `` meet the requirements of the military theory of the United States and NATO '' and `` promote the stability in the southern Balkan region . ''
<ENAMEX TYPE="OKAY">Italy , Turkey , Greece , Romania , Bulgaria , Macedonia , Albania and the United States are participating in the exercise</ENAMEX> .
